<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 3:00PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Iron County
through 330 PM MDT...
At 300 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Cedar City, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Cedar City and Enoch.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 15 between mile markers 58 and 68.
Utah Route 56 between mile markers 50 and 61.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
